lead_paragraph: Steven Matz didn't allow a run over five hitless innings and Yoenis Cespedes hit his first spring homer to lead the New York Mets past the Chicago Cubs 8-1 Friday and end a 14-game winless streak in their last exhibition game.

headline.print_headline: Matz Dominates, Mets Beat Cubs 8-1 in Final Spring Tuneup
